00:04:11.000 --> 00:04:15.000
components and study them on their own in a test tube.   

00:04:15.000 --> 00:04:19.000
They will take an organisms,  and to a biochemist wishing to study  

00:04:19.000 --> 00:04:23.000
the beauty of a butterfly flapping in the wind and understanding all of  

00:04:23.000 --> 00:04:28.000
the mechanics of how it could possibly flap those wings and all,   

00:04:28.000 --> 00:04:32.000
he or she would start by taking the butterfly, putting it in the blender,   

00:04:32.000 --> 00:04:36.000
pressing puree and making an extract,  and trying to purify individual  

00:04:36.000 --> 00:04:40.000
components that would explain muscles moving back and  

00:04:40.000 --> 00:04:45.000
forth and all that.  This is, of course,   

00:04:45.000 --> 00:04:50.000
a geneticist's point of view,  but it's all right.  You have Bob  

00:04:50.000 --> 00:04:55.000
who will represent biochemistry just fine.  And they want to purify out  

00:04:55.000 --> 00:05:00.000
individual components.  Individual components away from the  

00:05:00.000 --> 00:05:04.000
organism.  And the most important individual  

00:05:04.000 --> 00:05:07.000
type of component that they study are proteins because there are  

00:05:07.000 --> 00:05:10.000
zillions of proteins and they do all sorts of things in the body.   

00:05:10.000 --> 00:05:13.000
And so you could say, in some sense,  that this whole theme of  

00:05:13.000 --> 00:05:17.000
biochemistry, which got started at the turn of the 20th century,   

00:05:17.000 --> 00:05:20.000
really just a few years before the turn of the 20th century,   

00:05:20.000 --> 00:05:23.000
of grinding up an organism,  studying its components and being  

00:05:23.000 --> 00:05:26.000
able to find, for example,  I want to understand how I can  

00:05:26.000 --> 00:05:30.000
digest lunch.  Well.  Or how yeast can digest the sugar.   

00:05:30.000 --> 00:05:35.000
Grind up yeast, fractionate it and find some protein that's able to  

00:05:35.000 --> 00:05:40.000
digest the sugar all by itself without the rest of the organism,   

00:05:40.000 --> 00:05:45.000
an enzyme to do that.  That's the logic of biochemistry.   

00:05:45.000 --> 00:05:50.000
